        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: retry run history creation after transient coordinator failure",
        "body": "## Summary\n- retry coordinator run creation after transient pre-lease failures\n- keep one explicit pending-create state armed until a run record attaches, including across replacement leases\n- clear unavailable-history state after successful recovery\n- report lease-based recovery commands when run history remains unavailable\n\n## Validation\n- `go test ./internal/cli -run 'TestRunRecorder|TestPrintRunFailureDigest' -count=1`\n- `go test -race ./internal/cli`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `bash scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- project autoreview, local repair and full branch diff: no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Live proof\n- Built the PR head and routed a real coordinator-backed AWS Linux run through a localhost reverse proxy.\n- The proxy injected exactly one HTTP 503 for the initial `POST /v1/runs`, then forwarded subsequent requests unchanged.\n- Crabbox warned that run-history creation would retry, acquired the real lease, created and printed a run handle after lease attachment, ran `true` successfully, and released the lease.\n- Final coordinator inventory had no matching lease.\n\nRelease note: coordinator-backed `crabbox run` now retries transient run-history creation after a lease is available and preserves recovery across replacement leases.\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/483\n",
